>Description:
If you change, say, your color scheme
using <root window> | Properties | Appearance | Scheme,
the windows most apps (such as Netscape)
change their colors accordingly, but
DrScheme doesn't.
>How-To-Repeat:
Select ... | Scheme and change your default
scheme.  The panels containing the buttons
and indices at the top and bottom of DrScheme
don't change their appearance.
